# Frontend (Vite) build-time config. Copy to `.env` only if you need to override a default.
#
# OAuth is handled by same-origin Cloudflare Pages Functions at /auth, so the browser no longer
# needs a Google Client ID. You normally don't need any frontend env var at all.
#
# VITE_AUTH_BASE — where the auth Functions are mounted. Defaults to "/auth". Set it to an empty
# string to build a static-only variant with Google sign-in disabled (API-key-only mode).
# VITE_AUTH_BASE=/auth

# The Google client id + secret are SERVER-side secrets for the Pages Functions — never put them
# here. Set them on the Cloudflare Pages project (production) and in `.dev.vars` (local dev).
# See .dev.vars.example.
